<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>*massive spoilers*</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Pirmin ~ Karana ~">Pirmin ~ Karana ~</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:16 a.m. 4/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> *massive spoilers*<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/quest.cgi?read=328" TARGET=_self>Re: Screeming mace</A> (Kenson)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Head over to Crushbone. In one of the houses in the western part (I think) of the zone there are 2 dwarfen smiths and an elven priest, standing in separate booths. Hail the middle dwarf several times and You are on Your way. You need two items to get the Mace - A dwarfen mail (get it from the Emperor Crush - around lvl 18 mob, found in the castle) and a Bracer of battle (From the Warlord - around lvl 15 mob found both inside and outside the castle (random)). Now the Warlord is a pretty rare spawn - I spent about 8 hours RT searching for him and I only saw him ONCE during that time (and then he was already engaged). I ended up buying the bracers (I payed 25 Plat).

<P>For the more info (You need it on this quest) Check out EQ'Lizer:
<P>http://gameznet.com/eq/
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><EM><A HREF="http://gameznet.com/eq/" TARGET=_top>EQLizer</A></EM></P>
